data.a55d15a9-bd5d-11e9-9e9c-94659cf754d0:
Cemetery hosts a variety is issues.

1. A couple of grave markers and tombs are being engulfed by trees roots and/or being broken open. One tree has pushed a tomb open approximately 1.5 inches were currently there is 9 inches of water present inside of the 14 inch area.

2. A couple of ground grave markers are askew due to tree roots pushing them outwards.

3. An area near the Beth El section on the scemetery is totally under water!

4. One slab is broken open across with about a 2 inch gap. The gap from top to inside the grave is about 2 feet. Nothing unusual was visible.

5. There is a sloped area by a canal. This area is currently protected by gravel. One headstone is abourt 43 inches from the slope.

6. A couple of monuments have been toppled and left on the ground, while a large 6 foot cross is cracked all the way around.
